 color=#ffffff>(8/26/01 8:08:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A true epic battle</span><hr size=1> Is it just me, or is the Enraged Golem in Plane of Fear the ONLY true epic battle of all the various epic quests across the game.  Now, I'm not saying the golem is terrible difficult in comparison to the others, in fact, it's pretty easy.  BUT, look at how long the battle lasts compared to all the others.<br>
<br>
Venril Sathir goes down within 2 minutes, or wins and wipes people out, is that epic?  Does it seem like the battle lasts all that long?<br>
<br>
Any dragon used for epics is difficult, but it's not a long sustained battle, it's more like, &quot;go in, kick ass, or get ass kicked&quot;.  32k hit points isn't a lot when you look at the current damage output.<br>
<br>
The idea of an epic quest is one that is long, complex, and takes a long time to complete.  If they made each staff be a LONG set of subquests, all which lead to the final reward.  Is our quest really so long and complex?  Is there really any quest in EQ that is epic?  The Paladin quest, which requires working on other quests to complete is close, but in general, the only difficulty about the epics in the game is the rare spawns, and the rare drops.  An epic battle should be long and drawn out, throw 50 people at mobs that split, and split, and spawn new mobs, and have it an hour long straight fight.  THAT would be a true epic battle.  The Avatar of War is an epic battle, it lasts for a long time.<br>
<br>
Am I the only one that feels this way, that an epic quest should lead us around by the nose, with 75 steps, each of moderate difficulty, and with waypoints in the quest where you have made obviously significant progress?   <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 59 Wizard<br>
Bloodguard of Souls<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
